AB InBev’s Brito Receives 2010 Bonus of 3.16 Million Euros

-- B y   J o h n   M a r t e n s
-- 
2011-03-08T17:37:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/ab-inbev-s-brito-receives-2010-bonus-of-3-16-million-euros.html
  Anheuser-Busch InBev NV (ABI)  will pay
Chief Executive Officer Carlos Brito variable compensation of
3.16 million euros, the Leuven, Belgium-based brewer of Bud
Light and Stella Artois said in a  statement  on its website.
  Brito’s fixed salary was 1.24 million euros last year and he
also earned variable compensation of 3.13 million euros related
to AB InBev’s performance in the second half of 2009, according
to the statement. In addition, Brito was granted 273,365 stock
options with an strike price of 42.41 euros, which he can
exercise starting Nov. 30, 2015.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Martens at 
 jmartens1@bloomberg.net  